[3] California (Contra Costa County)
Date: Fri 9 May 20143
Source: KTVU [edited]
http://www.ktvu.com/news/news/local/contra-costa-county-sees-spike-whooping-cough-case/nfscD/


Contra Costa County has seen a jump in the amount of whooping cough cases in 2014, with 9 cases of the disease found in a single school. In fact, in Martinez, all but 2 of the schools have seen confirmed cases. Morello Park Elementary was the school with 9 cases, the highest number in the county so far.

There have been 49 cases of whooping cough or pertussis, across the county. The 9 at Morello Park account for almost 20 percent of the county total.

"So far we have had 4 babies hospitalized here in Contra Costa. Luckily, all are recovering," said the county's communicable disease programs chief Erika Jenssen. "But in 2010, when there was a big epidemic across California, 10 babies died throughout the state. And what we're really trying to do is protect the babies from pertussis."

[Byline: John Sasaki]

