[5] Pennsylvania (Allegheny County)
Date: Wed 14 May 2014
Source: WPXI [edited]
http://www.wpxi.com/news/news/local/11-cases-whooping-cough-confirmed-allderdice-high-/nfwSs/


So far 11 cases of whooping cough have been confirmed at Allderdice High School, Pittsburgh Public Schools spokeswoman Ebony Pugh said [Tue 13 May 2014]. Pugh said the 1st case was confirmed in April 2014.

After the 1st case was confirmed, a letter was sent home to the parents of anyone in a classroom or team with the student or anyone not vaccinated. Pugh said a letter went out to all parents after the 4th case was confirmed.

