[6] South Carolina (Pickens County)
Date: Mon 12 May 2014
Source: The Greenville News [edited]
http://www.greenvilleonline.com/story/news/local/2014/05/12/whooping-cough-causes-concern-pickens-county/8987555/


State health officials are asking health care providers to be on the watch for pertussis in Pickens County since there has been a spike in cases over the past few weeks. State health officials are asking health care providers to be on the watch for pertussis in Pickens County since there has been a spike in cases over the past few weeks.

At this time in 2013, there were 66 cases statewide. But of the 30 cases reported in the state so far in 2014, 13 have been in Pickens County, including 2 cases at West End Elementary and Forest Acres Elementary that were reported in March 2014, according to the state Department of Health and Environmental Control [DHEC].

There have been no cases in Greenville County and fewer than 4 cases each in Anderson and Spartanburg counties, DHEC reports. "So far this year [2014], we've received reports of more pertussis cases from Pickens County compared to any other county in the state," said Dr Riyadh Muhammad, a DHEC medical consultant and pediatrician. "Through all of 2013," she said, "there were 9 cases reported in Pickens County."

There were 24 231 cases of pertussis in 2013 nationwide, CDC reports. And DHEC reports 212 in South Carolina in 2013.

[Byline: Liv Osby]

